5000|$|It is not {{uncommon}} to find combination guns paired with sub-caliber inserts for the <b>shotgun</b> <b>barrels.</b> These inserts, usually 9 to 11 inches long, slip inside the <b>shotgun</b> <b>barrel(s)</b> and chamber rimfire cartridges such as the [...]22 LR or [...]22 Magnum. These further increase the flexibility of the guns, and will add considerably to the value.|$|E
5000|$|Combination {{guns are}} over/under designs, usually {{with a shotgun}} barrel over a rifle barrel. Iron sights are {{commonly}} used for aiming the rifle, and the front sight alone is sufficient to point the shotgun. Scope mounts are available, sometimes with a cutout for aiming the <b>shotgun</b> <b>barrels.</b> However, the thinness of the <b>shotgun</b> <b>barrels</b> that are usually on top make the scope mounting awkward.|$|E
